{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013HMwgDCiRLnNPPbmTZRNTm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sprint-state.json shows that epic-16 is already `done` with 8/8 stories done. But the sprint-status.yaml (which is derived from sprint-state.json) shows stories 16-7 and 16-8 at `review` and epic-16 at `backlog`. This is a reconciliation issue — sprint-state.json is the source of truth, and it says these stories are at `review`, not `done`.\n\nWait, looking more carefully:\n- sprint-state.json: 16-7 status = \"review\", 16-8 status = \"review\"\n\n\n- sprint-state.json: epic-16 status = \"done\", storiesDone = 8\n\nThat's contradictory — the epic claims 8/8 done but the individual stories are stuck at review. The git log shows a commit that marked these stories as done and completed the epic, but the working tree has uncommitted changes that seem to have reverted this. Since sprint-state.json is modified but not staged, the current state might be a regression. The session logs confirm both stories actually passed their reviews, so something's out of sync.\n\nThe real issue is that stories 16-7 and 16-8 are showing as review in both files, yet the epic says done — that's the inconsistency I need to resolve. The proof documents exist and the session logs show they completed verification, so I need to update their status to done and reconcile the epic state, but I should follow the harness-run process to do this properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13308,"cache_read_input_tokens":41109,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13308},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56e2f0c2-4a39-4ee3-9b6d-24dac6514cd2","uuid":"766bb130-9006-4b03-8efd-94b2f967671d"}
