{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016oMp5dyvi4z39ojf6UvsMD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01C2xgXX28PzBRD7RWctCRbL","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Run session retrospective","prompt":"Run /retrospective for the current sprint session.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --json` to get token consumption data.\n\nCRITICAL: Read the session issues log FIRST. This file contains real problems, workarounds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nCONTEXT: This was a no-op session. The parent orchestrator found all 74 stories across 16 epics already at `done`. The only work performed was state reconciliation — sprint-state.json had regressed (stories 16-7 and 16-8 reverted from `done` to `review`) due to ralph's state snapshot overwriting the committed version. The parent restored the committed state and updated sprint-status.yaml.\n\nThe session issues log contains entries from EARLIER sessions today (not this session), covering stories 16-5 through 16-8 code reviews and verifications. Use those for historical context but note they are from prior sessions.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — this was a no-op session with state reconciliation fix\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize the ralph state regression bug\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report, note this session was minimal cost. Include historical subagent token analysis from the session issues log for prior sessions today.\n4. **What went well** — all 74 stories complete, sprint done\n5. **What went wrong** — ralph state snapshot overwrote committed sprint-state.json\n6. **Lessons learned** — ralph state management needs to respect git committed state\n7. **Action items** — fix ralph state snapshot to not regress committed state\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":276,"cache_read_input_tokens":58721,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":276},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56e2f0c2-4a39-4ee3-9b6d-24dac6514cd2","uuid":"1153c171-b3b0-4520-aec9-13e9b3cc221d"}
