{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UNFK3wbNibXPgZmDSyd4yK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TAnv94XuUeuMNmnuwSbs5J","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat >> /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md << 'RETRO_EOF'\n\n---\n\n## Session 52 — Sprint Complete, No-Op #36\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28T16:59\n**Session:** 52\n**Sprint status:** COMPLETE — 74/74 stories done, 17/17 epics done\n**Productive work this session:** None. State reconciliation only.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Session Summary\n\nNo-op session. The parent orchestrator detected all 74 stories across 16 epics (plus epic 0) already at `done`. The only work performed was state reconciliation — `sprint-state.json` had regressed again (stories 16-7 and 16-8 reverted from `done` to `review`) because Ralph's state snapshot overwrote the git-committed version. The parent restored committed state and updated `sprint-status.yaml`. This is the 36th consecutive no-op session.\n\n### 2. Issues Analysis\n\n| Category | Issue | Severity | Occurrences |\n|----------|-------|----------|-------------|\n| State management | Ralph state snapshot overwrites committed sprint-state.json, reverting 16-5 through 16-8 from `done` to `review` | HIGH | 36 sessions |\n| State management | `ralph/status.json` still reports `stories_completed: 70` instead of 74 | MEDIUM | Persistent |\n| Phantom data | `1-1-foo` phantom story appears in cost tracking ($24.35 wasted) | LOW | Persistent |\n\n**Root cause (unchanged):** Ralph loads `sprint-state.json` at startup, caches it in memory, and writes it back on each loop iteration. The in-memory snapshot predates stories 16-5 through 16-8 reaching `done`. The `registerStory` guard added in session 22 prevents new phantom stories but does not prevent status reversion of existing ones.\n\n### 3. Cost Analysis\n\n#### Cumulative Sprint Cost (from `codeharness stats`)\n\n| Metric | Value | Delta from Session 51 |\n|--------|-------|-----------------------|\n| Total API-equivalent cost | $889.68 | +$172.83 |\n| Total API calls | 6,486 | +1,218 |\n| Average cost per story | $4.15 | +$0.61 |\n\n#### Cost Breakdown by Phase\n\n| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |\n|-------|-------|------|---|\n| verify | 3,803 | $473.01 | 53.2% |\n| orchestrator | 904 | $199.19 | 22.4% |\n| retro | 763 | $104.46 | 11.7% |\n| code-review | 397 | $45.89 | 5.2% |\n| create-story | 348 | $37.05 | 4.2% |\n| dev-story | 271 | $30.07 | 3.4% |\n\nVerification remains the dominant cost at 53.2%. Orchestrator overhead (22.4%) includes the repeated no-op sessions with state reconciliation.\n\n#### Cost Breakdown by Token Type\n\n| Type | Tokens | Cost | % |\n|------|--------|------|---|\n| Cache reads | 345.2M | $517.74 | 58% |\n| Cache writes | 12.4M | $232.81 | 26% |\n| Output | 1.9M | $138.91 | 16% |\n| Input | 15K | $0.23 | 0% |\n\nCache reads dominate (58%), which is expected and cost-efficient. Cache writes at 26% suggest frequent context loading across subagent spawns.\n\n#### Subagent Token Analysis (from session issues log — earlier sessions today)\n\nEight subagent runs were logged today for stories 16-5 through 16-8 (code review + verification for each):\n\n| Subagent Run | Tool Calls | Top Tools | Key Observation |\n|-------------|------------|-----------|-----------------|\n| 16-5 code review | 27 | Read:10, Grep:8, Bash:6 | `harness-run.md` read 5 times |\n| 16-5 verification | 15 | Bash:10, Read:5 | `npm test` run twice |\n| 16-6 code review | 19 | Bash:8, Read:7, Grep:3 | Story test file run 3 times |\n| 16-6 verification | 15 | ~8 files read | Minimal redundancy |\n| 16-7 code review | 22 | Read:9, Grep:8, Bash:7 | Two grep passes could merge |\n| 16-7 verification | 16 | Grep:10, Bash:7 | `npm test` run twice |\n| 16-8 code review | 18 | Read:11, Glob:4, Bash:3 | No redundancy |\n| 16-8 verification | 14 | Bash:7, Read:6, Edit:3 | `npm test` run twice |\n| **Totals** | **146** | | |\n\n**Waste patterns identified:**\n- `npm test` double-runs in 3 of 4 verification subagents (~$1.50 wasted per occurrence)\n- `harness-run.md` read 5 times in one subagent (should cache after first read)\n- Story test files re-executed multiple times during code review\n\n#### This Session's Cost\n\nThis session was minimal — parent orchestrator detected sprint complete, ran state reconciliation, generated this retro. Estimated cost: ~$3-5 (single orchestrator turn with retro subagent).\n\n### 4. What Went Well\n\n- **Sprint complete.** All 74 stories across 17 epics finished. 100% delivery.\n- **Earlier sessions today completed epic 16.** Stories 16-5 through 16-8 all passed code review and verification with zero items sent back for re-development.\n- **Code quality solid.** 96.85% test coverage, all 158 files above 80% floor. 4,020 tests passing.\n- **Subagent quality high.** All 8 subagent runs today (4 code reviews, 4 verifications) completed successfully. 41/41 acceptance criteria passed across stories 16-5 through 16-8.\n\n### 5. What Went Wrong\n\n- **Ralph state regression — 36th occurrence.** Same bug, same fix, 36 sessions running. Ralph's stale in-memory state continues to overwrite committed `sprint-state.json` every session.\n- **Cumulative waste from no-op sessions.** 36 sessions x ~$4-5 each = ~$144-180 wasted on state reconciliation and retros for a completed sprint.\n- **Retro file bloat.** This file is now 5,400+ lines and 285KB. Exceeds read tool limits. Previous retro recommended a 100KB cap — not yet implemented.\n\n### 6. Lessons Learned\n\n1. **Ralph state management must respect git committed state.** A monotonic status guard (never revert `done` to earlier status) would have prevented all 36 occurrences.\n2. **Sprint-complete early exit is critical.** If `done === total`, skip all subagent spawning. This single check would save ~$4-5 per no-op session.\n3. **Retro file rotation is overdue.** At 285KB, the retro file cannot be read in full by tools. Archive per-sprint or impose a size cap.\n4. **Subagent prompt optimization pays off.** The `npm test` double-run pattern in verification subagents is a simple prompt fix worth ~$1.50/story.\n\n### 7. Action Items\n\n#### Immediate (before next session)\n\n| # | Action | Owner |\n|---|--------|-------|\n| 1 | Add monotonic status guard to Ralph: never revert a `done` story to any earlier status | ralph/ |\n| 2 | Add sprint-complete early exit: if `done === total`, skip all subagent spawning | ralph/ |\n\n#### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n\n| # | Action | Owner |\n|---|--------|-------|\n| 3 | Rotate retro files — archive this 285KB file and start fresh | harness tooling |\n| 4 | Add per-session cost delta tracking to `codeharness stats` | codeharness CLI |\n| 5 | Fix `npm test` double-run pattern in verification prompts | verification prompts |\n\n#### Backlog\n\n| # | Action | Owner |\n|---|--------|-------|\n| 6 | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story ($24.35 in cost tracking) | state management |\n| 7 | Fix 5 pre-existing BATS failures in `all_tasks_complete` suite | tests |\n| 8 | Address LOW-priority code review items deferred from epic 16 | tech debt |\nRETRO_EOF","description":"Append session 52 retrospective to existing retro file"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":661,"cache_read_input_tokens":26016,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":661,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01C2xgXX28PzBRD7RWctCRbL","session_id":"56e2f0c2-4a39-4ee3-9b6d-24dac6514cd2","uuid":"2449dbee-4dda-4416-a144-ede7ae51fcee"}
